I"E<h3 id="force-to-use-virtualenv-python">Force to use virtualenv python</h3>
<p>When running modules that require virtualenv, such as Azure, local_action or localhost connection sometimes still  use the  default /usr/bin/python</p>

<div class="language-yaml highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="s">localhost ansible_python_interpreter=python</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>now localhost will run python from the activated virtualenv.
<a href="http://www.zigg.com/2014/using-virtualenv-python-local-ansible.html">See this</a></p>
:ET